         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ I am informed by Mr. Fitzgerald ¶  that Captain Broomfield assured him of the occurrence of the Dendrobium, figured in the  ¶ Australian Orchids ¶  as D. superbiens, on the Prince of Wales' Group, ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">84.07.00b</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Gardeners' Chronicle</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from '<name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>' in 'Home correspondence', </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle</seg>
                     <seg style="">, 16 August 1884, p. 214 (B</seg>84.08.01). It is dated to early July as the latest likely date for the letter to have been sent, to have been included in this issue.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am informed by Mr. Fitzgerald<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> that Captain Broomfield assured him of the occurrence of the Dendrobium, figured in the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australian Orchids</seg> as D. superbiens, on the Prince of Wales' Group, about 20 miles from the mainland of Queensland, and 50 miles from New Guinea,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. in Torres Strait.</p>
               </note> and he adds that it is also to be found sparingly on the nearest mainland of Australia.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. Fitzgerald (</seg>1875-94), vol. 2, tab. 70. The <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle</seg> had reviewed the first part of vol. 2 in the issue of 10 May 1884, p. 609, identifying <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. superbiens</seg> as a Queensland species, whereas Fitzgerald had written that the specimen figured was obtained from North Queensland.</p>
               </note> Captain Broomfield cultivates this splendid Orchid, and he considers it superior to all his others in this — that it is the only one absolutely always in flower, a raceme being obtainable at any time. </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">F. v. M.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>
            </p>
         </div>
